UGHELLI – An Ijaw leader, Chief Julius Babogha, has blamed the un­derdevelopment of the Niger Delta region on its leaders that had held sensitive positions in government. Babogha, the Group Man­aging Director/Chief Execu­tive Officer, Tamfel Global Re­source, in a statement, said to develop the region, a ministry was created. He stressed that the Minis­try of the Niger Delta Affairs was not created by President Muhammadu Buhari admin­istration. ABUJA DOCTOR REVEALS HOW MOST NIGERIA MEN ARE NOW OVERCOMING TERRIBLE BEDROOM PERFORMANCE DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. DON'T BE A VICTIM! He said since the ministry’s creation, several people from the Niger Delta region were made ministers and heads of the ministry with the aim of bringing development, lamenting that they failed. He stressed: “I can tell you that the real problem is not Bu­hari, but his lieutenants and aides, among whom are people from the Niger Delta, recruit­ed for developmental purpos­es, but failed to perform. Ogriagbene Community Tasked On Protection Of Govt Assets Christian Group Blames Insecurity, Corruption On Poor Leadership “But, this is not to exempt or exonerate the president totally. He too has failed the Niger Delta region, because up till today, he cannot show vividly one area he has devel­oped in the region. Even the East-West road that has been awarded years before his as­sumption of office, could not be constructed.” SHOCKING! DOCTORS ARE MESMERIZED BY THIS NATURAL PREMATURE EJACULATION AND SMALL SIZE SOLUTION GUARANTEED TO BULLDOZE YOUR WOMAN INTO SEXUAL SUBMISSION